content.description: Topping out is crux.  Would not trust center hollow flake.
A low start to Cheers to Voyager.  Start with low sidepulls from a sit.  A hard opening move (probably with the left hand) leads to more tricky climbing and a dabby but manageable finish.
content.protection: Pads, a couple for sure, maybe 3.

content.description: Start low on right lay-back rail and work your way up face to comfy top-out.  A couple variations you can do on this boulder.
content.location: Up hill and directly behind Bruised by about 30 feet.

content.description: Right arete and face. Crux is high (last move). I sat started, but had to dig out a rotten pile of leaves to do so and I don’t think a sit adds anything.
content.protection: Pads.  I'm told the sharp big rock in the landing zone has been relocated, so probably not PG13 any more, YMMV.
content.location:
See main page and GPS coordinates on beta photo.  This boulder is 5-6 minute walk west and slightly south of Bird Foot Buttress.  Walking down the social trail on the main directions it will be 30 feet to your left half way down from the top of the bluff to the bottom. 

  Alternatively, the easiest and most direct way to this boulder is as follows:  Park at the CCC trailhead and walk 100-200 yards east on the road until you come to a culvert going under the road with a sign on either side of the road. Head left (north) up the drainage.  This becomes a faint trail and about halfway up to the top of the bluff you will see this boulder 30 feet off to your right.

content.description: Start left hand side pull middle of face in cave.  Right hand jug on right arete.  Work out right side of roof.  A few moves, mantle, freedom.
content.location: 30 feet north west of Dazed boulder

content.description: Sit start on left arete. Climb straight up.
content.location:
Left of Dazed and Contused.  Same boulder.   

  Park at the CCC trailhead and walk 100-200 yards east on the road until you come to a culvert going under the road with a sign on either side of the road. Head left (north) up the drainage.  This becomes a faint trail and about halfway up to the top of the bluff you will see this boulder 30 feet off to your right.

content.description: A clutch of boulders in a wooded boulder field, low on the bluff at the bottom of a drainage.
